<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-96-0733 </DOCNO><TEXT>The authors establish criteria for determining the viability of the probabilisticestimation of the mechanical properties and time to failure of steelsused as structural materials in thermal power plants via the statisticalcomputer processing and simulation of mechanical and destructive testingdata accumulated over time. The purpose of their model is to narrow thewindow of uncertainty as closely as possible in order to be able to forecastreliably the service life and operating safety of thermal power plantcomponents for a given number of mechanical property input parameters.</TEXT></DOC>